title: For Sale:  1916 Spanish Mauser
postcontent: Oviedo Model 1916. 1925 Manufacture. 7mm Mauser caliber.The 1916 Mauser, offered by surplus dealers, was thought to have dried up over 30 years ago. With the 2016 bankruptcy sale of SAMCO, a major importer, 5000 of these rifles were discovered.Packed away in crates, since the '70's, and preserved in cosmoline, this was a major find. Although most 1916's are encountered in .308 caliber, the original reciever was not intended for modern commercial .308 chamber pressure. Original 7x57 Mausers in good condition are rare.This rifle is hand picked from one of the first batches to be released. It is a "First Pattern" with the rare "lange vizier" roller coaster rear sight.It has been completely disassembled. All cosmoline removed, and oiled. The wood has been cleaned, and treated to a coat of Linseed oil.There is NO pitting of the metal,which retains 75% of the original blueing. Bore has strong rifling. Wood has no cracks, and normal handling marks.All numbers match, reciever, barrel, floorplate, rear sight...excecpt the bolt, which is normal for these surpluse rifles.The original stamping  (Crown, "Fabrica de Armas Oviedo" and the year of manufacture  1925) are on the receiver.A great find for a historical example, a cheap "Truck Gun", or a fun shooter.I have fired 20 rounds through it. It functions smooth, and is accurate. 7mm ammo is plentiful in all grains.Supplies of this rifle, in this condition, are going fast.Original sling included.FTF Alabama residents only.
